  "text": "To speed up the construction efficiency, we introduce the concept of Canonical Ordering to guide the propagation of wavefronts. The application of Canonical Ordering has been recently discussed to speed up best-first search in grids-based pathfinding tasks in [CITATION_1] . Different from the classical Dynamic Brushfire algorithm, which expands all the eight directions at every step, Canonical Ordering can eliminate redundant, symmetric paths from the source of state change, which accounts for the main part of the speed improvement.",
